{"type":"text","text":"{
  "id": "196c03644425d8e2",
  "subject": "Key Insights & Assets for Our Upcoming Marketing Campaign",
  "from": "mcp.test.dki2@gmail.com",
  "date": "Sun, 11 May 2025 09:38:24 -0700",
  "snippet": "Hi Sarah, I pulled together the most relevant information from our internal notes, analytics and recent e-mails so you have everything you need in one place as we finalize the campaign plan. ──────────",
  "body": "Hi Sarah,\n\nI pulled together the most relevant information from our internal notes, analytics and recent e-mails so you have everything you need in one place as we finalize the campaign plan.\n\n────────────────────────────────\n1. Audience & Segment Insights\n────────────────────────────────\n• Gen Z (18-26)\n  – 81 % interact exclusively through mobile; top features are in-app account opening & remote check deposit.\n  – 63 % would switch banks for a better budgeting tool; gamified savings challenges over-index (+27 pp).\n  – Short-form video with influencers on TikTok/IG Reels performs 3× better than static ads.\n\n• Millennials (27-42)\n  – Largest share of mortgage pre-approvals (42 %) but cite underwriting speed as the main friction.\n  – Cross-sell opportunity: Rewards Credit Card within 90 days of mortgage close lifts LTV +34 %.\n  – Financial-wellness e-mails on debt-to-income management get 18 % CTR.\n\n• Gen X (43-58)\n  – 54 % start online but finish in-branch/phone; value a hybrid experience.\n  – Strong appetite for wealth-building tools; robo-advisor adoption balances are 2× higher than average.\n  – Bundling robo-advisor with low-fee HELOC messaging improved conversion by 21 % in A/B test.\n\n• Boomers (59+)\n  – Trust & estate webinars up 47 % YoY; 73 % want phone follow-ups.\n  – Direct-mail with QR to pre-schedule branch appt. delivers 4.1 % response (vs. 2 % industry avg).\n\n• Small-Business Owners\n  – 56 % cite fast working-capital access as top pain-point; same-day micro-loans have 92 % CSAT.\n  – Educational content on SBA 7(a) eligibility gets 2× engagement vs generic ads.\n\n────────────────────────────────\n2. Creative & Channel Recommendations\n────────────────────────────────\n• Gen Z/Millennial: 30-sec vertical videos demoing instant check deposit & budgeting tools; TikTok, IG Reels.\n• Gen X: Geo-fenced mobile ads within 2 mi of branches promoting in-person financial check-ups.\n• Boomers: Fold-out direct mail + QR to book branch meetings; emphasise FDIC, fraud protection & live help.\n• Small Biz: LinkedIn how-to pieces + case-study carousel ads on time-saving invoicing & same-day loans.\n\nEarly-Stage KPIs we’ll track:\n  – App downloads & first-time logins (Gen Z/M).\n  – Branch appointment bookings (Gen X/Boomer).\n  – Product-specific: HELOC starts, high-yield savings opens, business-checking leads.\n\n────────────────────────────────\n3. Performance Benchmarks (Last Campaign)\n────────────────────────────────\n• Total impressions: 1,254,678\n• Click-through rate: 3.45 %\n• Conversion rate: 2.15 %\n• Revenue generated: $78,420\nThese numbers are broadly in line with targets but highlight room to optimise CTR and post-click conversion.\n\n────────────────────────────────\n4. Q1 Campaign Strategy Snapshot\n────────────────────────────────\nFocus: Deepening engagement with existing customers via segmented e-mails + paid social.\nKey Tactics:\n  1. Persona-based content calendars (weekly cadence).\n  2. Dynamic creative that swaps headlines/visuals by age cohort.\n  3. Look-alike retargeting built from our most profitable segments.\n  4. Incremental tests on incentive offers (cash vs reward points) to find lift drivers.\n\n────────────────────────────────\n5. Next Steps\n────────────────────────────────\n• Confirm priority segments/products for creative briefing by EOD Friday.\n• Finalise incentive matrix & budget allocations.\n• Schedule 30-min sync (Thurs or Fri) to walk through the data and lock messaging.\n\nLet me know if you’d like any deeper cuts—e.g. raw data tables, heat-maps of app feature usage, or persona slide decks—and I’ll send them right over.\n\nLooking forward to collaborating!\n\nBest regards,\n[Your Name]\n"
